30// This class encapsulates all information required to access a certain element.
31class ElementAccessInfo final {
32 public:
33 ElementAccessInfo(ZoneVector<MapRef>&& lookup_start_object_maps,
34 ElementsKind elements_kind, Zone* zone);
35
36 ElementsKind elements_kind() const { return elements_kind_; }
37 ZoneVector<MapRef> const& lookup_start_object_maps() const {
38 return lookup_start_object_maps_;
39 }
40 ZoneVector<MapRef> const& transition_sources() const {
41 return transition_sources_;
42 }
43
44 void AddTransitionSource(MapRef map) {
45 CHECK_EQ(lookup_start_object_maps_.size(), 1);
46 transition_sources_.push_back(map);
47 }
48
49 private:
50 ElementsKind elements_kind_;
51 ZoneVector<MapRef> lookup_start_object_maps_;
52 ZoneVector<MapRef> transition_sources_;
53};
54
55// This class encapsulates all information required to access a certain
56// object property, either on the object itself or on the prototype chain.
57class PropertyAccessInfo final {
58 public:
59 enum Kind {
60 kInvalid,
61 kNotFound,
62 kDataField,
63 kFastDataConstant,
64 kDictionaryProtoDataConstant,
65 kFastAccessorConstant,
66 kDictionaryProtoAccessorConstant,
67 kModuleExport,
68 kStringLength
69 };
70
71 static PropertyAccessInfo NotFound(Zone* zone, MapRef receiver_map,
72 OptionalJSObjectRef holder);
73 static PropertyAccessInfo DataField(
74 JSHeapBroker* broker, Zone* zone, MapRef receiver_map,
75 ZoneVector<CompilationDependency const*>&& unrecorded_dependencies,
76 FieldIndex field_index, Representation field_representation,
77 Type field_type, MapRef field_owner_map, OptionalMapRef field_map,
78 OptionalJSObjectRef holder, OptionalMapRef transition_map);
79 static PropertyAccessInfo FastDataConstant(
80 Zone* zone, MapRef receiver_map,
81 ZoneVector<CompilationDependency const*>&& unrecorded_dependencies,
82 FieldIndex field_index, Representation field_representation,
83 Type field_type, MapRef field_owner_map, OptionalMapRef field_map,
84 OptionalJSObjectRef holder, OptionalMapRef transition_map);
85 static PropertyAccessInfo FastAccessorConstant(
86 Zone* zone, MapRef receiver_map, OptionalJSObjectRef holder,
87 OptionalObjectRef constant, OptionalJSObjectRef api_holder);
88 static PropertyAccessInfo ModuleExport(Zone* zone, MapRef receiver_map,
89 CellRef cell);
90 static PropertyAccessInfo StringLength(Zone* zone, MapRef receiver_map);
91 static PropertyAccessInfo Invalid(Zone* zone);
92 static PropertyAccessInfo DictionaryProtoDataConstant(
93 Zone* zone, MapRef receiver_map, JSObjectRef holder,
94 InternalIndex dict_index, NameRef name);
95 static PropertyAccessInfo DictionaryProtoAccessorConstant(
96 Zone* zone, MapRef receiver_map, OptionalJSObjectRef holder,
97 ObjectRef constant, OptionalJSObjectRef api_holder, NameRef name);
98
99 bool Merge(PropertyAccessInfo const* that, AccessMode access_mode,
100 Zone* zone) V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
101
102 void RecordDependencies(CompilationDependencies* dependencies);
103
104 bool IsInvalid() const { return kind() == kInvalid; }
105 bool IsNotFound() const { return kind() == kNotFound; }
106 bool IsDataField() const { return kind() == kDataField; }
107 bool IsFastDataConstant() const { return kind() == kFastDataConstant; }
108 bool IsFastAccessorConstant() const {
109 return kind() == kFastAccessorConstant;
110 }
111 bool IsModuleExport() const { return kind() == kModuleExport; }
112 bool IsStringLength() const { return kind() == kStringLength; }
113 bool IsDictionaryProtoDataConstant() const {
114 return kind() == kDictionaryProtoDataConstant;
115 }
116 bool IsDictionaryProtoAccessorConstant() const {
117 return kind() == kDictionaryProtoAccessorConstant;
118 }
119
120 bool HasTransitionMap() const { return transition_map().has_value(); }
121 bool HasDictionaryHolder() const {
122 return kind_ == kDictionaryProtoDataConstant ||
123 kind_ == kDictionaryProtoAccessorConstant;
124 }
125 ConstFieldInfo GetConstFieldInfo() const;
126
127 Kind kind() const { return kind_; }
128
129 // The object where the property definition was found.
130 OptionalJSObjectRef holder() const {
131 // TODO(neis): There was a CHECK here that tries to protect against
132 // using the access info without recording its dependencies first.
133 // Find a more suitable place for it.
134 return holder_;
135 }
136 // For accessor properties when the callback is an API function with a
137 // signature, this is the value that will be passed to the callback as
138 // FunctionCallbackInfo::Holder().
139 // Don't mix it up with holder in a "object where the property was found"
140 // sense.
141 OptionalJSObjectRef api_holder() const { return api_holder_; }
142 OptionalMapRef transition_map() const {
143 DCHECK(!HasDictionaryHolder());
144 return transition_map_;
145 }
146 OptionalObjectRef constant() const {
147 DCHECK_IMPLIES(constant_.has_value(),
148 IsModuleExport() || IsFastAccessorConstant() ||
149 IsDictionaryProtoAccessorConstant());
150 return constant_;
151 }
152 FieldIndex field_index() const {
153 DCHECK(!HasDictionaryHolder());
154 return field_index_;
155 }
156
157 Type field_type() const {
158 DCHECK(!HasDictionaryHolder());
159 return field_type_;
160 }
161 Representation field_representation() const {
162 DCHECK(!HasDictionaryHolder());
163 return field_representation_;
164 }
165 OptionalMapRef field_map() const {
166 DCHECK(!HasDictionaryHolder());
167 return field_map_;
168 }
169 ZoneVector<MapRef> const& lookup_start_object_maps() const {
170 return lookup_start_object_maps_;
171 }
172
173 InternalIndex dictionary_index() const {
174 DCHECK(HasDictionaryHolder());
175 return dictionary_index_;
176 }
177
178 NameRef name() const {
179 DCHECK(HasDictionaryHolder());
180 return name_.value();
181 }
182
183 private:
184 explicit PropertyAccessInfo(Zone* zone);
185 PropertyAccessInfo(Zone* zone, Kind kind, OptionalJSObjectRef holder,
186 ZoneVector<MapRef>&& lookup_start_object_maps);
187 PropertyAccessInfo(Zone* zone, Kind kind, OptionalJSObjectRef holder,
188 OptionalObjectRef constant, OptionalJSObjectRef api_holder,
189 OptionalNameRef name,
190 ZoneVector<MapRef>&& lookup_start_object_maps);
191 PropertyAccessInfo(Kind kind, OptionalJSObjectRef holder,
192 OptionalMapRef transition_map, FieldIndex field_index,
193 Representation field_representation, Type field_type,
194 MapRef field_owner_map, OptionalMapRef field_map,
195 ZoneVector<MapRef>&& lookup_start_object_maps,
196 ZoneVector<CompilationDependency const*>&& dependencies);
197 PropertyAccessInfo(Zone* zone, Kind kind, OptionalJSObjectRef holder,
198 ZoneVector<MapRef>&& lookup_start_object_maps,
199 InternalIndex dictionary_index, NameRef name);
200
201 // Members used for fast and dictionary mode holders:
202 Kind kind_;
203 ZoneVector<MapRef> lookup_start_object_maps_;
204 OptionalObjectRef constant_;
205 OptionalJSObjectRef holder_;
206 OptionalJSObjectRef api_holder_;
207
208 // Members only used for fast mode holders:
209 ZoneVector<CompilationDependency const*> unrecorded_dependencies_;
210 OptionalMapRef transition_map_;
211 FieldIndex field_index_;
212 Representation field_representation_;
213 Type field_type_;
214 OptionalMapRef field_owner_map_;
215 OptionalMapRef field_map_;
216
217 // Members only used for dictionary mode holders:
218 InternalIndex dictionary_index_;
219 OptionalNameRef name_;
220};

222// Factory class for {ElementAccessInfo}s and {PropertyAccessInfo}s.
223class AccessInfoFactory final {
224 public:
225 AccessInfoFactory(JSHeapBroker* broker, Zone* zone);
226
227 base::Optional<ElementAccessInfo> ComputeElementAccessInfo(
228 MapRef map, AccessMode access_mode) const;
229 bool ComputeElementAccessInfos(
230 ElementAccessFeedback const& feedback,
231 ZoneVector<ElementAccessInfo>* access_infos) const;
232
233 PropertyAccessInfo ComputePropertyAccessInfo(MapRef map, NameRef name,
234 AccessMode access_mode) const;
235
236 PropertyAccessInfo ComputeDictionaryProtoAccessInfo(
237 MapRef receiver_map, NameRef name, JSObjectRef holder,
238 InternalIndex dict_index, AccessMode access_mode,
239 PropertyDetails details) const;
240
241 // Merge as many of the given {infos} as possible and record any dependencies.
242 // Return false iff any of them was invalid, in which case no dependencies are
243 // recorded.
244 // TODO(neis): Make access_mode part of access info?
245 bool FinalizePropertyAccessInfos(
246 ZoneVector<PropertyAccessInfo> infos, AccessMode access_mode,
247 ZoneVector<PropertyAccessInfo>* result) const;
248
249 // Merge the given {infos} to a single one and record any dependencies. If the
250 // merge is not possible, the result has kind {kInvalid} and no dependencies
251 // are recorded.
252 PropertyAccessInfo FinalizePropertyAccessInfosAsOne(
253 ZoneVector<PropertyAccessInfo> infos, AccessMode access_mode) const;
254
255 private:
256 base::Optional<ElementAccessInfo> ConsolidateElementLoad(
257 ElementAccessFeedback const& feedback) const;
258 PropertyAccessInfo LookupSpecialFieldAccessor(MapRef map, NameRef name) const;
259 PropertyAccessInfo LookupTransition(MapRef map, NameRef name,
260 OptionalJSObjectRef holder,
261 PropertyAttributes attrs) const;
262 PropertyAccessInfo ComputeDataFieldAccessInfo(MapRef receiver_map, MapRef map,
263 NameRef name,
264 OptionalJSObjectRef holder,
265 InternalIndex descriptor,
266 AccessMode access_mode) const;
267 PropertyAccessInfo ComputeAccessorDescriptorAccessInfo(
268 MapRef receiver_map, NameRef name, MapRef map, OptionalJSObjectRef holder,
269 InternalIndex descriptor, AccessMode access_mode) const;
270
271 PropertyAccessInfo Invalid() const {
272 return PropertyAccessInfo::Invalid(zone());
273 }
274
275 void MergePropertyAccessInfos(ZoneVector<PropertyAccessInfo> infos,
276 AccessMode access_mode,
277 ZoneVector<PropertyAccessInfo>* result) const;
278
279 bool TryLoadPropertyDetails(MapRef map, OptionalJSObjectRef maybe_holder,
280 NameRef name, InternalIndex* index_out,
281 PropertyDetails* details_out) const;
282
283 CompilationDependencies* dependencies() const;
284 JSHeapBroker* broker() const { return broker_; }
285 Isolate* isolate() const;
286 Zone* zone() const { return zone_; }
287
288 JSHeapBroker* const broker_;
289 TypeCache const* const type_cache_;
290 Zone* const zone_;
291
292 AccessInfoFactory(const AccessInfoFactory&) = delete;
293 AccessInfoFactory& operator=(const AccessInfoFactory&) = delete;
294};
